{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2013}} {{Use South African English|date=January 2013}} '''''S v Van Zyl'''''<ref>1987 (1) SA 497 (O).</ref> is an important case in [[South African law]], heard in the Orange Free State Provincial Division by Steyn J and Malherbe J on 10 February 1986, with judgment handed down on 27 February. The court found that the crime of [[arson]] can be committed by a person who sets fire to his own [[immovable property]] with the intention of harming another in his property.
